commit.message: Merge branch 'master' of github.com:sirjaren/redoflacs

Fix configuration version check

* Amended reporter user name

This regression was introduced in commit:
c1b0c3d763b596161e12ad92acb80133c43fb8c1

Thanks to @peioe for the report.

Fix configuration version check

This regression was introduced in commit:
c1b0c3d763b596161e12ad92acb80133c43fb8c1

Thanks to @Peio for the report.

Separate internal help to man page

_long_help():
  Documentation on program execution has been moved to a separate man
  page, making documentation and 'redoflacs' easier to manage.

  Additionally, this change allows package maintainers to provide
  a bundled man page with distribution of 'redoflacs'.

Simplify error logging

_create_log():
  Removed; the abstraction of error logging was not worth the cognitive
  load required to use the function.  Instead, all abstractions are
  removed and the logging is done each flac operation's function.

Minor tweaks to how logging is done by specifying the log file first
before 'printf' arguments.

Simplify header in log files

_create_log():
  Less whitespace and characters are created, making the log files more
  minimal and to the point

_short_help():
  Removed dependency on 'cat'.

Format whitespace, copyright, license and comments

This changes from TABs to SPACEs.  Additionally, comments have been
updated to reflect this change (tabbed heredocs).

License has been changed to MIT from GPL2.
Update copyright year

Added documentation about '-x, --no-extra-tags'

_long_help():
  Added an entry for the '-x, --no-extra-tags' option.

  NOTE's added to '-c, --compress' and '-C, --compress-notest' detailing
  the changes to these operations with the new argument.

  Bumped the documentation revision

Added new option (-x, --no-extra-tags)

This option allows a user to run the compression option (-c,
--compress) without setting the COMPRESSION upon successful compression.

_check_conflicting_operations():
  There is now a check to make sure this new option is NOT called with
  (-C, --compress-notest).  This option is essentially invalidated with
  this new option.

Documention to follow

Minor tweaks and simplification

_find_artwork():
  Simplify building $artwork_blocks[@], by removing the process
  substitution and 'mapfile' wrapper

Use ANSI-C like strings to handle the color escapes.  This will make
it possible to put the color variables in the 'printf' arguments

Use 'nproc' to determine the number of jobs to use

_find_cores():
  Since 'nproc' is part of GNU Coreutils, prefer to use it when
  determining the number of jobs.  Fallback to /proc/cpuinfo if
  not available.

  Removed array instantiation, preferring to just loop directly
  over /proc/cpuinfo

Update copyright and bump version

Included minor change to platform checking (for Cygwin)

Documentation added and bumped the config revision

Helped explain the various values accepted for the new
'preserve_modtime' option, and incremented the script and configuration
revision version to allow users to be aware of the new changes.

Merge branch 'YetAnotherNerd'

Thanks to YetAnotherNerd, we are now able to preserve file mtime when
doing non-destructive operations (metaflac vs flac).

Thanks!
add option to preserve file mod times
remove unnecessary if
Update README with redoflacs 0.30 screenshot

Update to version 0.30

Fix incorrect declaration of array

Remove superfluos newlines on script invocation

As a result of switching to a short range operator test, the printf's
were executed independent of the test.

Forcing the printf's to be executed as a statement conditional to the
testing, fixes this issue.

Update configuration file

With the changes to redoflacs since the last release, this commit fixes
a variety of spelling errors and cleans up the format somewhat.  The
structure has been slightly changed, as well as the REVISION number
format at the bottom of the configuration.

The way the configuration is generated is a bit more sane, created by a
hereodoc.  Escaping of special characters (double quotes, backticks,
etc) is no longer required and should make it easier to maintain.

There are also minor tweaks in determining the script revision and
configuration revision number, and as such, the configuration revision
number has been incremented.

Filename format of spectrograms to use a suffix

This is to make generated files more inline with other parts of the
script (log files, extracted artwork, etc).

The help/man page has been updated to reflect this change.  Other minor
tweaks have been made to the man page as well (spelling, grammar, etc).

Documented VORBIS_COMMENT tag field specification, including support for
tag fields to have whitespace as a valid character.

Fix broken handling of TRACKNUMBER/TRACKTOTAL tags

Regarding previous commit: 60080632924ae4ca65a8d584dae78bf0960b5a24

Strip the leading and trailing whitespace from the TRACKNUMBER and
TRACKTOTAL tags, BEFORE we try and prepend the zero (if specified in the
user configuration).

Restore prepended and appended whitespace removal

Per the _current_ redoflac documentation:
  A benefit of this operation is it's ability to remove any extra spacing
  before and after tag values. For example, let's say you have a FLAC file
  with a TITLE tag of (minus the single quotes):

  '    The Great Escape    '
  After retagging, the TITLE tag would look like (minus the single quotes):

  'The Great Escape'

This commit restores that functionality (did it ever exist?).

All tag values are now explicitly read in and stripped of prepended/appended
whitespace (spaces, tabs etc) before being re-applied to a FLAC file.

Greatly speed up '_retag_*' functions

Partial revert of: a537a28300a1de0cfc5e15c8bb4bbd850dd03911

_retag_analyze() and _retag_apply():
  In the previous commit (mentioned above), the way stored tag fields
  were sent to 'metaflac' resulted in a massive slowdown of analyzing
  tags and setting them.  This was necessary, though in order to have
  'metaflac' properly handle whitespace in VORBIS COMMENT fields.

  This new commit reverts to sending a printed array of tag fields
  directly to 'metaflac', like before, only now, the quoting of the tag
  fields is done properly in an array, to allow 'metaflac' to interpret
  any and all tag fields, including whitespace.

Remove '--no-error-on-compression-fail' argument

This argument is no longer needed and as such, causes flac-1.3.0 users
(non-git), and below to fail when verifying FLAC files during
compression.

flac-1.3.0 (and below):
  This argument doesn't exist, and the failure this is meant to prevent
  doesn't exist, so this argument is removed.

flac-1.3.0 (git):
  Shortly after the release of 1.3.0, developers added in the above
  option, '--no-error-on-compression-fail'.  This was meant to prevent
  the encoder from exiting with a non-zero exit code, due to new
  changes.

  The changes were to error on compression if the ratio was >1.000,
  since compression side of the encoding actually didn't result in any
  gain (failure).

  The above option would force the encoder to give a 0 exit code, making
  the error a "warning" since the encoding was successful, just not the
  compression ratio (ie, not a smaller file size).

  The developers soon realized the above option wasn't all that great,
  and created a new one called '--error-on-compression-fail'.  This is
  to "opt-in" to the non-zero exit code.  Now, if the ratio from
  compression is >1.000, a warning message will display but the exit
  code will be 0, by default.  Using the new argument, people can opt to
  have a non-zero exit code.  The original argument is still maintained
  for compatibility (doesn't do anything right now).

  Going forward, redoflacs is omitting the above two options, as this is
  not considered an error when verifying FLAC files.

  Users running a version of FLAC 1.3.0 (from git) may have issues if
  it's a version which has the first argument, but not the second. Since
  the FLAC version in question is development stage software, it's
  unreasonable for redoflacs to support it, since the way going forward
  in FLAC has been defined.

To summarize, the removal of '--no-error-on-compression-fail' argument
allows redoflacs to function appropriately for all users of FLAC
(non-git), as is intended.

Whitespace changes

Convert from space indentation, back to tab indentation, so others can
configure their development environments to their liking.

Fix quoting with `metaflac' and cleanup

_retag_analyze() and _retag_apply():
  `metaflac' does not accept sending quoted strings inside an array or
  string as part of an argument (multiple arguments specified).  As a
  result, the previous quoting broke it's effectiveness, leading to
  false logs detailing missing tags.

  The quoting is necessary in order to properly handle spaces in tag
  fields (the tag field, not the tag value).  Spaces are a valid
  character for VORBIS COMMENTS fields, though they are extremely rare.

  A result of this fix/refactoring, will make these functions perform a
  bit slower.

_print_progress():
  Minor cleanup and enforce the parent directory is displayed for files
  and directories, if directory called on the command line is '.' or
  './'.

NOOP: Continuity changes to code only

Cleaned up placement of semicolon placement to be consistent.

Use single quotes whenever a string, expression, statement is NOT
to be evaluated.

Opening brace for functions is now on a newline by itself.

Change function names from '__foo()' to '_foo()'

The original logic for prepending function names with two undersocres
no longer applies.  Instead, the switch from two underscores to one,
seems to be most widely accepted as a way to indicate locality.

This script will use that convention.  A single underscore details
locality to the script itself, not local to a function or statement.

_aucdtect() was renamed to _aucdect_cmd() to not interfere with this
new change.

_sox() was renamed to _sox_cmd() to also not interfere with this new
change.
